NOTE="css-images top-level suite exposed via the modulePrefixes [\"\"] entry in wpt.json (subdirectories gradient / image-set / animation / image-orientation / parsing are follow-up); testharness computed-value tests are filtered out by isScriptHarnessTest, leaving 322 layout-gradeable reftests. Gradient painting is layout-trivial so the pass rate measures replaced-element (object-fit / object-position / object-view-box) sizing robustness. 312 of 322 pass, including the two #68 outliers that are now fixed: gradients-with-border.html (border-box vs content-box on gradient backgrounds) and the sibling-index() cases (linear-gradient-sibling-index / conic-gradient-color-with-sibling-index). The 10 known failures are separate residuals: (1) body/root height collapsing to 0 in the no-paint case where Crater falls back to the 600px viewport default -- linear-gradient-body-sibling-index (browser height=0 / crater=600) and svg-script-is-ignored (browser=19.2 / crater=600); (2) contain-intrinsic-size combined with object-fit on a replaced element (the 4 object-fit-containcontainintrinsicsize-png-001* tentative tests, browser height=71.2 / crater=38.4); (3) object-view-box fill on <canvas> (object-view-box-fit-fill-canvas, browser=442.6 / crater=480); and (4) writing-mode interacting with object-view-box (object-view-box-writing-mode-canvas height 125 vs 150, -img / -svg width 19.2 vs 0). Pins 312/322 as a no-regression gate; closing the residuals is follow-up work. Deterministic across two runs. Measured with the vendored Tinos text metric (tests/wpt-fonts)."
